Facts (layer 2):

`Foo : type` (TypeDefinition):
  has definition constraints
  has type `Foo`
  is a definition

`Foo : type` (TypeDefinition):
  has definition constraints
  has type `Foo`
  is a definition

`show` (VariableExpression):
  has bound(s) `Describe` `Foo` (resolved as `default error instance (Describe value)`)
  has type `Foo -> ()`
  is an expression
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `show :: value -> () where (Describe value)`

`show Foo` (ExpressionStatement):
  has type `()`

`show Foo` (CallExpression):
  has type `()`
  is an expression

`Foo` (ConstructorExpression):
  has type `Foo`
  is an expression
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `Foo : type`



Feedback:

`show` (error-instance)

  Can't describe `Foo`.
  
  You can't display `Foo` on the screen or use it in placeholders because
  it can't be converted into a string.
